# Angular Infinite Loop & Memory Leak Prevention

## CRITICAL: Lessons from BUG-124.19 Investigation

⚠️ **This rule prevents catastrophic refresh loops that can make applications completely unusable**

Based on comprehensive investigation of a persistent refresh loop that evaded 6 fix attempts, these patterns are **MANDATORY** for Angular applications.

## 🚨 CIRCUIT BREAKER PATTERN - REQUIRED

### Always Implement Loop Detection for Critical Methods

```typescript
// REQUIRED: Circuit breaker for any method that can be called frequently
class ComponentWithFrequentMethods {
  private circuitBreaker = new InfiniteLoopDetector();
  
  criticalMethod(): void {
    if (!this.circuitBreaker.checkLoop('criticalMethod')) return;
    // Method implementation
  }
}

class InfiniteLoopDetector {
  private calls = new Map<string, number>();
  private timestamps = new Map<string, number>();
  private maxCalls = 10;
  private timeWindow = 5000;

  checkLoop(method: string): boolean {
    const now = Date.now();
    const lastTimestamp = this.timestamps.get(method) || 0;
    
    if (now - lastTimestamp > this.timeWindow) {
      this.calls.set(method, 1);
      this.timestamps.set(method, now);
      return true;
    }
    
    const callCount = (this.calls.get(method) || 0) + 1;
    this.calls.set(method, callCount);
    
    if (callCount > this.maxCalls) {
      console.error(`🚨 INFINITE LOOP DETECTED in ${method}!`);
      return false;
    }
    
    return true;
  }
}
```

## 🚫 TEMPLATE ANTI-PATTERNS - NEVER DO THESE

### ❌ PROHIBITED: Method Calls in Templates
```html
<!-- PROHIBITED - Causes infinite change detection loops -->
<div [ngClass]="getResponsiveClass()">
<mat-icon [style.font-size]="getIconSize()">
<div [style.grid-template-columns]="getGridColumns()">
```

### ✅ REQUIRED: Computed Properties
```typescript
// REQUIRED: Compute once, use getter in template
export class Component {
  private _responsiveClass = '';
  private _iconSize = '24px';
  private _gridColumns = 3;

  // Compute only when state changes
  private updateResponsiveProperties(): void {
    this._responsiveClass = this.computeClass();
    this._iconSize = this.computeIconSize();
    this._gridColumns = this.computeGridColumns();
  }

  // Use getters in template
  get responsiveClass(): string { return this._responsiveClass; }
  get iconSize(): string { return this._iconSize; }
  get gridColumns(): number { return this._gridColumns; }
}
```

```html
<!-- CORRECT - Uses computed properties -->
<div [ngClass]="responsiveClass">
<mat-icon [style.font-size]="iconSize">
<div [style.grid-template-columns]="'repeat(' + gridColumns + ', 1fr)'">